The Nasarawa State Government has commenced preparations towards hosting President Muhammadu Buhari, who will visit the state on a two-day working visit next month. Governor Abdullahi Sule disclosed this yesterday during the first state expanded executive council meeting. According to the governor, information has reached the state government indicating that President Buhari is billed to visit Nasarawa State on February 17 and 18.   Hanifa: Justice must be done, Ganduje insists     Ugwuanyi receives ‘Most Peaceful Governor in…     Soludo seeks modest inauguration, says govt   To this end, Governor Sule said adequate preparation is being put in place to welcome the President. “With that announcement, there are certain things we have to put in place, to accord the President a deserved welcome,” he stated. - Advertisement - He commended members of the state executive council, particularly commissioners, who are doing their best to assist the administration to deliver dividends of democracy to the people. The governor expressed his satisfaction with the performance of some of the commissioners who hit the ground running after their inauguration.